TITLE: Implementing Concrete ExprPcodeExecutorStatePiece and BytesExprPcodeExecutorState
DESCRIPTION: Provides concrete implementations of the abstract state piece class and creates a paired executor state combining concrete byte storage with symbolic expressions. The ExprPcodeExecutorStatePiece supplies space creation logic while BytesExprPcodeExecutorState pairs concrete and abstract state pieces.
SOURCE: https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra/blob/master/GhidraDocs/GhidraClass/Debugger/B4-Modeling.md#2025-04-06_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public static class ExprPcodeExecutorStatePiece
		extends AbstractExprPcodeExecutorStatePiece<ExprSpace> {
	public ExprPcodeExecutorStatePiece(Language language) {
		super(language);
	}

	@Override
	protected AbstractSpaceMap<ExprSpace> newSpaceMap() {
		return new SimpleSpaceMap<ExprSpace>() {
			@Override
			protected ExprSpace newSpace(AddressSpace space) {
				return new ExprSpace(space);
			}
		};
	}
}

public static class BytesExprPcodeExecutorState extends PairedPcodeExecutorState<byte[], Expr> {
	public BytesExprPcodeExecutorState(PcodeExecutorStatePiece<byte[], byte[]> concrete) {
		super(new PairedPcodeExecutorStatePiece<>(concrete,
			new ExprPcodeExecutorStatePiece(concrete.getLanguage())));
	}
}
```

