TITLE: Initializing FunctionGraph Class in Java for Ghidra
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the FunctionGraph class, which extends AbstractProgramGraph. It includes constructor parameters for a Program and Function, suggesting it's used to create a graph representation of a specific function within a program being analyzed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra/blob/master/Ghidra/Features/FunctionGraph/README.md#2025-04-06_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class FunctionGraph extends AbstractProgramGraph<CodeBlock> {

	private Function function;
	private Program program;
	private FunctionGraphInfoProvider infoProvider;

	public FunctionGraph(Program program, Function function) {
		this(program, function, true);
	}

	public FunctionGraph(Program program, Function function, boolean includeInstructions) {
		super(program);
		this.program = program;
		this.function = function;
		if (includeInstructions) {
			buildGraph();
		}
		else {
			buildGraphNoInstructions();
		}
	}
```

