TITLE: Implementing GhidraDebuggerISF Class for Debugging in Python
DESCRIPTION: This code defines the GhidraDebuggerISF class, which extends DebuggerISF. It implements methods for instruction handling, register operations, and memory access for debugging purposes in Ghidra.
SOURCE: https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra/blob/master/Ghidra/Debug/Debugger-isf/README.md#2025-04-06_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Python
CODE:
```
class GhidraDebuggerISF(DebuggerISF):
    def __init__(self, **kwargs):
        super(GhidraDebuggerISF, self).__init__(**kwargs)

    def get_register(self, name):
        return self.api.getRegisterValue(name)

    def set_register(self, name, value):
        self.api.setRegisterValue(name, value)

    def get_memory(self, address, size):
        return self.api.readMemory(address, size)

    def set_memory(self, address, data):
        self.api.writeMemory(address, data)

    def step(self):
        self.api.step()

    def continue_execution(self):
        self.api.resume()

    def break_execution(self):
        self.api.break_()

    def get_next_instruction(self):
        return self.api.getNextInstruction()

    def get_instruction_string(self, instruction):
        return self.api.getInstructionString(instruction)

    def get_instruction_operands(self, instruction):
        return self.api.getInstructionOperands(instruction)

    def get_instruction_mnemonic(self, instruction):
        return self.api.getInstructionMnemonic(instruction)
```

