TITLE: Parsing and Printing Game Board in Ghidra Debugger Script
DESCRIPTION: This code parses the read memory data to extract game board dimensions and prints the locations of mines.
SOURCE: https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra/blob/master/GhidraDocs/GhidraClass/Debugger/B3-Scripting.md#2025-04-06_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
int width = ByteBuffer.wrap(widthDat).order(ByteOrder.LITTLE_ENDIAN).getInt();
int height = ByteBuffer.wrap(heightDat).order(ByteOrder.LITTLE_ENDIAN).getInt();
for (int y = 0; y < height; y++) {
	for (int x = 0; x < width; x++) {
		if ((cellsData[(y + 1) * 32 + x + 1] & 0x80) == 0x80) {
			println("Mine at (%d,%d)".formatted(x, y));
		}
	}
}
```

