TITLE: Implementing createTable() Method for SampleTablePlugin in Java
DESCRIPTION: This method creates a TableChooserDialog, configures its properties, and populates it with sample data. It demonstrates how to set up columns, add rows, and customize the table's appearance and behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra/blob/master/Ghidra/Extensions/SampleTablePlugin/README.md#2025-04-06_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
private void createTable() {
	TableChooserDialog tableDialog = createTableChooserDialog("Sample Table", "Sample Table", this,
		tool, false, new SampleDataSource());
	tableDialog.addCustomColumn(new AddressColumn());
	tableDialog.addCustomColumn(new StringColumn());
	tableDialog.setPreferredSize(new Dimension(400, 300));
	tableDialog.setRememberSize(false);
	tableDialog.setModal(false);

	TableChooserTableModel<SampleRowObject> model = tableDialog.getTableModel();
	SampleRowObject row1 = new SampleRowObject(addr("0x01001000"), "First Entry");
	SampleRowObject row2 = new SampleRowObject(addr("0x01002000"), "Second Entry");
	SampleRowObject row3 = new SampleRowObject(addr("0x01003000"), "Third Entry");
	model.addObject(row1);
	model.addObject(row2);
	model.addObject(row3);

	tableDialog.show();
}
```

