TITLE: Implementing Graph Building Methods in Java for Ghidra's FunctionGraph
DESCRIPTION: These methods, buildGraph() and buildGraphNoInstructions(), are responsible for constructing the function graph. The former likely includes detailed instruction-level information, while the latter creates a more abstract representation without individual instructions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra/blob/master/Ghidra/Features/FunctionGraph/README.md#2025-04-06_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
private void buildGraph() {
	CodeBlockModel blockModel = new BasicBlockModel(program);
	CodeBlockIterator blockIterator =
		blockModel.getCodeBlocksContaining(function.getBody(), monitor);
	while (blockIterator.hasNext()) {
		CodeBlock block = blockIterator.next();
		addVertex(block);
		CodeBlockReferenceIterator destinations = block.getDestinations(monitor);
		while (destinations.hasNext()) {
			CodeBlockReference reference = destinations.next();
			CodeBlock destBlock = reference.getDestinationBlock();
			addEdge(block, destBlock);
		}
	}
}

private void buildGraphNoInstructions() {
	BasicBlockModel basicBlockModel = new BasicBlockModel(program);
	CodeBlockIterator blockIterator =
		basicBlockModel.getCodeBlocksContaining(function.getBody(), monitor);
	while (blockIterator.hasNext()) {
		CodeBlock block = blockIterator.next();
		addVertex(block);
	}

	BlockEdgeInfo[] blockEdges = getBlockEdges();
	for (BlockEdgeInfo blockEdge : blockEdges) {
		CodeBlock sourceBlock = blockEdge.getSourceBlock();
		CodeBlock destBlock = blockEdge.getDestinationBlock();
		addEdge(sourceBlock, destBlock);
	}
}
```

