TITLE: Analyzing Mine Placement Algorithm in C
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the decompiled logic for the mine placement algorithm in the termmines program. It uses consecutive calls to rand() to determine mine positions, placing them on a board represented by a byte array, marking mines by setting the high bit (0x80) of the corresponding byte.
SOURCE: https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra/blob/master/GhidraDocs/GhidraClass/Debugger/A3-Breakpoints.md#2025-04-06_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
while (iVar2 = DAT_00604164, iVar1 = DAT_00604160, iVar10 < _DAT_00604168) {
  iVar3 = rand();
  iVar2 = DAT_00604164;
  iVar11 = rand();
  lVar7 = (long)(iVar11 % iVar2 + 1) * 0x20 + (long)(iVar3 % iVar1 + 1);
  bVar14 = *(byte *)((long)&DAT_00604160 + lVar7 + 0x1c);
  if (-1 < (char)bVar14) {
    iVar10 = iVar10 + 1;
    *(byte *)((long)&DAT_00604160 + lVar7 + 0x1c) = bVar14 | 0x80;
  }
}
```

