TITLE: Implementing init() Method for SampleTablePlugin in Java
DESCRIPTION: This method initializes the plugin by creating a new action and registering it with the tool. It sets up the action's name, description, and key binding for user interaction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra/blob/master/Ghidra/Extensions/SampleTablePlugin/README.md#2025-04-06_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
@Override
protected void init() {
	DockingAction action =
		new DockingAction("Sample Table", getName()) {
			@Override
			public void actionPerformed(ActionContext context) {
				createTable();
			}
		};
	action.setToolBarData(new ToolBarData(Icons.TABLE_ICON, null));
	action.setEnabled(true);
	action.setDescription("Sample Table");
	action.setKeyBindingData(new KeyBindingData(KeyEvent.VK_T, InputEvent.CTRL_DOWN_MASK));
	tool.addAction(action);
}
```

